caption: Excellent pizza in a neat urban space. Some of the pizzas are relatively simple but with excellent ingredients.

Last weekend, I heard their Pepperoni, and it was the best! My mates and I had lunch here. The service was great and fast. The crust on the pizza was super crunchy and not so sticky. It's been better mixed with soda. They're selling pizza slices here, and there's a massive serving. I can hardly eat the pizza.

The best customer service in town! This is well-known for their professional restaurant service. The food is of exceptional quality, and it is complemented by outstanding service. The pasta was great, and the sauce was delicious. We also tried salad and other flavors, all of which were excellent. The cost is manageable. This is something I would recommend to everyone.

Best pizza in Chicago. Great ingredients cooked in a coal fired oven give the pizza a unique taste. They normally have the pizza ready within 15 minutes of calling them. Staff are great there as well.

Pizza (which I would not wait to dine-in for pre Covid) was delicious -- as per usual. But the Burrata and broccolini? OMG. Beautifully odd and perfectly seasonal, a white sphere of Burrata wreathed with perfectly sauteed broccolini, then decorated with a substanstial 'streusel' of dried black currants and pine nuts. I mean their pizza is awesome... but this? This here? This Burrata? The one I've eaten half of and not going to share with you? Incomparably delicious, crunchy, savory, slightly sweet and creamy -- perfect answer to COVID blues.

Local pizza place open by two awesome guys. (David & Bill)    It comes as no surprise that this pizza has been awarded one of Chicago's Best by Chicago magazine. And I have also seen two different Pizza tour trucks making a stop here as I grabbed one to go on my way home. Fresh ingredients like fresh mozzarella, basil spinach with homemade sauce ,homemade crust done in a coal-fired oven. You can make your own  pie  or choose one of their delicious specialties  pizzas . so delicious just talking about it is making me hungry. The very first time I went  they made me feel like I was a regular. Everyone from the server's, cashier's, Cooks and the owners the whole staff  makes you feel like a VIP  or a member of the family . Grab one of the many delicious salads thén move on to your choice of pie. order one for yourself take the rest home. it'll be a nice snack later when you're wishing you had more you'll have it:-) :-) and then grab a delicious dessert provided by local merchants. They won me over with  the pizza  I kept me coming back because of the great service . One of my favorite Chicago spots doing the light modern thin crust worthy of Mama Nona. It's also a great place to grab grub on your way to a concert or sporting events as they are conveniently located less than 5 minutes away.

Love the Fiorentino with sausage... Was better with whole roast garlic.

My favorite pizza in all of Chicago, nothing can compare to Coalfire's thin crust in my opinion. I love the honey and salami and the vodka meatball, but I have enjoyed everything on the menu that I have tried. Since the crust is thin, I highly recommend eating in as it can be soggy if you take it home or get delivery.
Yummy pizza and fast 👍
awesome thin crust
We ordered a black and white goat cheese black garlic and chive pizza. But couldn't taste any black garlic. The pizza was thin and nicely done in the coal oven.
Great pizza. Lots of interesting take on flavours, on a delicately chewy thin base.
Best thin crust pizza in Chicago!
Awesome selection of toppings. Fresh and loaded with flavor!!  There was exceptional service here as well. I would come again.      $$$
I go to Chicago every thanksgiving  with my son and are first stop is coal fire pizza. great pizza I tell everyone one about it. great service .cant wait for thanksgiving again
My favorite pizza in the city.  Thin crust, high-quality ingredients, big on flavor and not overly filling.
The perfect set up. The pizza came out fast and the service was great! And the flavors of the pizzas were bursting. I’ll be going back soon.
Awesome food
Best pizza in Chicago!

I ordered the Bacon Jam. It was a great adventure of taste. The taste of the tomato, the chili peppers, the honey and the sage struck a delicate harmony. Especially the sage, which was quite a surprise, it adds another layer to the already complex flavor of the pizza. The dough was very crispy straight out of the stone oven. I will definitely come back for more.
Delicious pizza. Great for a chill date night or with family.
Great pizza!  we'll definitely be going back!
Great pizza, with a quiet environment to eat.
Delicious thin crust pizza baked in a coal fire oven! A must when we're in chicago
The pistachio pesto is delicious.
Great wood fire oven pizzas with original recipes and high quality toppings. I would recommend eating in the restaurant, the pizza is best right out of the oven.

Dec2017 Update: just had its Broccolini Burrata salad. Very very good. An excellent fix to a fairly weak non-pizza lineup....   One of the gems in a town of many great pizza outlets.  Lighter, crisper than traditional pizza, but still fulfilling as any great pizza should.

Lighting is low, not that it was a bad thing.  This pizza was def. amazing! Perfect perfect perfect. Lots of different options.  Originally I thought this place served 12 in pizzas for individuals, but you can only order a 16" size. Also, no splitting checks, so if you're with friends, only one can pay.  The servers were VERY attentive, and it's not as expensive as you would think. I'm def coming back here!
Good food.
Delicious
Best pepperoni pizza in The City where pizza is king! The other pizza where very good, but not great. I wish we could give a 4.4 stars.

I love their pizza but will not order takeout again. For the second time in a row, I ordered take out and arrived to find my pizza sitting on the hostess stand getting cold. Their pizza does not reheat well - pretty disappointed!
Pretty cool place, but they only serve pizza.
Super crowded, fast turnover, super tasty.
Wow!! This place was great! One of the best pizzas I have had. Atmosphere and service was just as good. Will definitely be back. Chicago's hidden gem.
Coalfire is my top 5 pizza in the city,  but so disappointed they no longer offer bacon.  Wont stop me from coming! Best eaten at the restaurant,  it's so thin it'll be cold by the time you get home.
Best thin crust pizza inChicago... owner is very friendly. Recommend the pizza with whipped ricotta.

Bruv the pizza is really tasty and it is boneless. It also good that the pizza is done in like 5-10 min so u can eat it sooner. Good job with ur pizza!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

Great thin and chewy crust with a little char on the edges. We had the black & white and the vodka meatball last time we were in and everyone loved it. The staff is friendly and attentive. I recommend dining in vs delivery because the thin crust doesn't hold the heat well. They also have a good bottled beer selection.

Delicious pizza. It's thin crust, and they make it very quickly. What's great is that you're not left with a super heavy feeling after eating here. It's very light. My favorites are the margherita, pistachio pesto, and the white garlic pizza.

I have been eating at Coalfire for ten years. The pizza is always fresh. Prosciutto and arugula is my favorite. The staff is very courteous without being intrusive. With all the pizza in Chicago Coalfire is a must!
Wonderful thin crust pizza!
Great pizza, lovely people  😊
Tasty stuff
Great pizza, nice staff!
Best pizza in the city but also crazy nice staff. Total win.
Great tasting pizza
Great pizzas but limited options for anyone who does not eat pork. Would be great if they had a few chicken options.  Very few appetizers on the menu as well.
N'duja pizza was delicious. The place could use better lighting and more appetizers on the menu.
Fast and friendly service great pizza
Owner is friendly and love the unique style
Great pizza. And fast!
Great food and atmosphere
The best 🍕
Great pizza, quick turn around. Will be back.
Good Pizzas . Salads . Desserts .
Great thin crust pizza with a decent beer selection.
Best pizza

The pizza was absolutely delicious . Service was equally great. I'm glad I came here from Indiana to try this pizza because it was worth it. The Mexican coke is also amazing. I will definitely be coming back.
Went there on a pizza tour.  Very tasty and delicious.
interesting flavors of pizza, but nothing overly impressive.
This place is amazing for a fast, delicious pie. He toppings are tradional and fresh. Great service by the staff and a cozy atmosphere. A great treat when you are feeling pizza.
Quick Delicious thin neopolitan pizza. Try the pepperoni ricotta.
Had the spinach pizza which was tasty. Good beer selection.
Great thin crust pizza.  Try the salami and honey.
Great pizza.  Please come to Deland Fl!
Best pizza that I like
Great service & awesome pizza! Friendly guys willing to go out of their way to help a customer.
Coalfire is a good pizza spot if you're in the area but I wouldn't travel to get there
It was really good pizza. I had the Lasagna Pizza which is their best rated and I enjoyed it. I think the sausage was very tasty but it made the pie a bit dry. Maybe a little more sauce.
Super-thin crust pizza.  Very simple and delicious.  My favorite brick oven style pizza in Chicago.
Been coming here since the beginning, 10 years ago!  great food and excellent service! Best place hands down!
Just great pizza!

Great quality pizza, texture of the dough is perfect and the sauce is not overly sweet. My favorite is the button pepperoni with ricotta. Will change your life. Place can get crammed and gets hot in the summer. Parking is pretty easy so if you have a car feel free to drive.
Best thing crust pizza!!! Really fresh and since it's cooked really quick! And it's super delicious. Love it!!!!
Fantastic pizza!!! Try it!!
Very good pizza.
Delicious pizza. Grabbed a pie for lunch and had plenty of time for drinks.
Awesome... Alona and Victoria were great... Pizza, unequaled.
Simply incredible.  Wait staff is friendly and the pizza is second to none.
Not Chicago style deep dish, but some great brick oven fired pizza.

This is what I call 'foofy' pizza, i.e. thin crust with toppings beyond standard pepperoni, sausage, onions, etc. It's super good. They look huge and you'll want to share 1 among 2-3 people but you'll be wrong. You WILL eat a whole one. I saw a 3.5 year old inhale 3/4 of one. My 11 month old ate a slice & a half. Toppings are great and I love super thin crust.
Fast, Delicious, and reasonably priced! The honey & salami was incredibly good.
Good change of pace from your typical pizza places. Crust has a nice char. Great balance from the bitterness mixed with sweet and savory from fresh classic toppings.
Best Pizza in Chicago.
Great place to have dinner
Great atmosphere and even better pizza. The 'Nduja was amazing.
Fantastic
My favorite pizza place of the ultra-thin variety. Great Caesar's salad and they have local desserts from Chicago Cupcake or Bang Bang Pie.
Favorite thin crust in Chicago.
1st time in chicago and this place is amazing.
Neopolitan pizza in one of its finest. You won't get better than this for many miles.
This is my favorite pizza in the city. It's always delicious. My favorite pizza is the lasagna.
Delicious, and fast service!
Cool, courteous staff. Badass pizza creations. Check it out if you're in West Town!
Cute (sometimes loud) environment. Pizza does take a bit to get, and it's not "wow" at first bite. It's a rare kind of food that gets better as you eat it.
Very tasty thin pizza.
My favorite pizza in Chicago. Great local riff on a New York pie. Decent selection of wine by the glass. Southport location is bigger, but the service here is always great.
Wish I would've come sooner! A fantastic ambiance, friendly staff and delicious pizza. What more could you ask for.
Very Thin and Very Fast Pizza. Great stop before a blackhawk game
My favorite pizza in Chicago. Thin crust with great sauce. The coal fire cooks it quick with a bit of char.  Service is always great.
